Oct 23 2009 	Second Stay - updating earlier review	This was my second stay at the Stratford, which shows you that I liked it well enough to stay there again. The rooms seem to have gotten a minor upgrade since last year. There was a new LCD television on the wall. This bathroom was nicer than the one I had last year - I'm not sure if it was renovated, or if it was this particular room. The rooms in this hotel are not all the same - layout varies according to the location and type of room. This one had a bathtub, while last year's just had a shower. I do wish that there had been some drawers - there was a small closet, but some stuff I had to leave in the suitcase. The Hilton is down the street and more than twice the price - if you want Hilton amenities, go there. If you want a clean comfortable place to sleep at a good price, the Stratford fills the bill.Hey Stratford - the continental breakfast is okay, but I just stayed in a Days Inn that had a wider assortment of pastries and apples and oranges. Surely you can do as well as Days Inn.	
