Sep 25 2009 	Perfect for the price	We stayed at the Stratford for four nights last week and found the hotel to be very good value for money. To be honest, for the price that we paid we weren't really sure what we could expect. The rooms were very clean, with newly decorated and spotlessly clean en-suite bathrooms. Beds were comfortable and the hotel staff were very helpful. We stayed in a &quot;deluxe double/double&quot; room which had 2 full sized beds. With 3 adults staying in the room space was a little restricted but with the little time that we did spend in our room this wasn't too much of an issue for us. The hotel is in a great central location right next to Union Square, getting there from the airport is easy with a BART stop just down the street. Breakfast was a nice addition, although expectations should be realistic for the price paid, it is a basic continental provision with muffins, toast, coffee and orange juice but it serves it's purpose well. The only down side would be the fact that the hotel didn't have air conditioning, at most times of the year in San Francisco I'm sure this isn't too much of a problem. However, we happened to be staying during the one week of the year that SF was experiencing a heat wave! We did find our room got pretty hot at night and with Powell Street being a main street it was too noisy to open the window. When we addressed this with the reception staff they were very helpful and tried to find us another room at the rear, but as we needed a room for 3 this wasn't possible (all rooms at the rear of the hotel are smaller rooms) the issue was resolved when they presented us with a large portable fan for our room - this helped make the room much more bearable. Speaking with other people during our visit we found that this was a problem at many hotels in SF that week as air conditioning really isn't generally a necessity in SF, this isn't therefore a criticism of The Stratford, merely a point to note. Overall, we had a very good stay and I would certainly consider returning.	
