Sep 7 2009 	Bargain price in a fabulous location	Generally, we would recommend the Hotel Stratford to people going to San Francisco and on a budget. It's in a great location - literally a half a block from Union Square, surrounded by fabulous shopping, and two blocks from the cable cars &amp; BART. We rented what they call the Family room - it has two adjoined rooms with a queen bed &amp; two doubles between them, as well as one smallish bathroom - and we got a very good price compared to what we would have had to pay elsewhere to be able to sleep the same number of people. Two drawbacks: the hotel does not have airconditioning (like many others in SF) and we were there during a heat wave, AND the room facing Powell Street was fairly noisy. However, these were balanced by the fact that the staff at the desk were very knowledgeable of the area, and there were several choices for VERY early morning breakfasts since we were still on East Coast time and out the door at 5 each day. Another fun thing for our children was that we were literally the only Americans we met staying there - everyone else was from a different country so they got to hear lots of different languages.We will be back in SF in two years and will plan to stay at the hotel again, assuming nothing changes with the ownership / pricing. It's a really solid choice, in my opinion.	
