Jan 22 2009 	Great little place	This a small boutique hotel in a great location. The Stratford is right on Powell Street. Down the bottom of the street is the cable car turn-around - which takes you to fisherman's wharf. Warning: the lines here are HUGE. If you walk up the hill a bit, you can usually jump on on a car fairly easily. Also down the bottom of Powell is a train station and a shopping mall. Great shopping is located nearby. Union Square is also a less than a block away. We stayed for 6 nights. Breakfast is included - but beware it is quite average. Only cereal and muffins. Coffee is not very nice either. The rooms are quite small - but clean. Only drawback of our particular room was we had no window on to the street. Just a wall of the next building! Being on level 1 we still experience quite a bit of street noise. Front desk staff were friendly and helpful. This is a good hotel for location and price. We would probably try something else next time though.	
Jan 3 2009 	Great value!	The Stratford is an older hotel that has recently been renovated. So, the rooms are quite small and the elevator is slow. Other than that, though, it's a great deal -- it's very clean, the decor is recent and tasteful in an IKEA kind of way, and the location can't be beat for tourism. I stayed in room 704, which had a great view down Powell St.; though the noise from the street might be pretty bad on the lower floors, it was barely audible on that level. Breakfast was a little stingy, but I'm fine with coffee and granola, so it did what I needed it to do. Seriously, San Francisco has lots of fleabag hotels, but this isn't one of them.	
