May 4 2007 	A Pleasant Experience!!!- April 22	From the moment my husband and I arrived at this hotel, the staff was superb and super helpful in recommending places to eat, parking our car, checking us in early. We stayed here one night (April-21) but we were going to spend the second day in San Francisco as well. So the hotel was kind enough to hold our luggage for the whole day (2nd day) while we went sightseeing. The young man at the reception desk was one of the most helpful people we found in San Fran. He recommended us great places to eat. For example, he recommended a Thai restaurant where we had lunch and it is located around the corner from the hotel on Ellis Street. It was very delicious and very affordable prices for San Francisco. The hotel location is just wonderful- it couldn’t be better. We loved having everything close by. All the nice shops were nice to have close by and even if you don’t like to shop, you are super close to Chinatown, also to get to the Wharf, you only walk a couple of blocks to bus station and get on BUS 30 to go to the Wharf in a few minutes. We love the location of this hotel and we would definitely stay here again. We found a great price in their webpage so I booked directly with them rather than via internet. We compared prices and booking directly with the hotel was cheaper than Orbitz, hotels.com, expedia, etc, etc. Our price was a packaged that included room for 1 night, continental breakfast, valet parking and Cable car tixs. The Valet parking service was wonderful; the breakfast was ok (typical of a continental breakfast) pastries, juice, nuts. The Cable car tix was a $5 value (per person) and it was a nice way to ride around the city once since it was cold. After seeing how much parking cost around San Fran, this was definitely a great perk to have our car valet parked at the same location where we were staying. About the rooms, we stayed in Room #817, our room view was to Ellis Street- no so great but we were not there to complaint about the view if everything else in the hotel was great. The room &amp; bathroom were very small (see pictures of room &amp; bathroom) but CLEAN (most importantly to us) and comfortable enough to sleep at night. My only discontent was the heater. San Francisco was cold in April and the hotel room had an ancient heater that it was hard to work out, even after calling the receptionist they explained to us how to turn it out but it seemed that it turned off by itself in the middle of the night so we woke up a bit cold. Like I said, it was not a big deal- it was definitely manageable. My husband and I really enjoyed our 1 night stayed in this hotel and we would definitely stay here again when we come back to San Francisco as it is a very pretty city.	
